reviews.text: Home away from home.  Mostly English.  Fr. Romanos is a gem.
The Greek Festival that they host is a nice chance to experience Greek cuisine.  They also have live music and greek merchandise.  The next festival is in February 2019

Pan-Orthodox Liturgy in several languages with English predominately. Everyone is truly welcome here. Ancient Christianity in practice here in a modern American city. If you'd like to see the Church as preserved from the Apostolic age, Orthodoxy is the place. If St Elizabeth the Wonderworker Orthodox Church had a website with update schedules for Divine Liturgy and Holy Days, I'd give it 5/5. So show up on Sundays a little before 10am.

It is a small but vibrant community of believers practicing the ancient faith. Just be warned, if you have never been to an Orthodox Christian service before, there is a lot of standing; wear comfortable shoes. Also for beginners, the morning prayers, Orthros, may be a little confusing; begin with the liturgy which starts at 10 am.
Good food, lots of friendly people.

A great diversion for the whole family. The butterfly atrium is amazing. The augmented reality foyer is a treat for the kids. The fossil collection walk in extremely enlightening.( I didn't know how "Giant" a giant ground sloth was. The Native Tribes of Florida exhibit is a must see. AND that's just part of it, don't forget to check out the Nature trails. Definitely worth the time and little bit of money.

The museum really has something for everyone.  There is a charge to enter The butterfly museum Which in our opinion was well worth it. There is a great section on the history of Florida, another section on historic animals and sea-life. There was plenty of exhibits and it’s not a museum that you can rush through and really enjoy all that it has to offer.

This museum has well-designed exhibits that are diverse, so everyone can find something they like there, from dinosaurs to shells and butterflies. We just volunteered on the Montbrook dig, so it was great to see the exhibit detailing the finds there. This museum is not isolated from current field work. Very exciting! We will be back. Give yourself plenty of time here. At least 3 hours.

Fun for all ages. You can have a new experience each time you come to explore. There are changing exhibits as well as permanent installation. Hidden treasures in unexpected places are fun for children and adults to explore. Access is easy for all levels of mobility.

Honestly, there should be an entrance fee for the amount of stuff that you get to see. With the care given to the exhibits there is no reason that they shouldn't charge. It is a great place for family's as well as adults without kids. Looking at the website and some of the photos I thought it might have been more geared towards younger kids, but it was great for all ages. If you have a free day and are looking for something to pass the time, this would be a great option.
Stopped though this quaint little town on a roadtrip to Cedar Lakes Botanical Gardens. It was the most quiet and peaceful town I've ever been in! Kinda reminded me of Storybrook from Once. 🤫

Fresh local food, nice and friendly people. The market is in a nice neighborhood, clean and tidy.Most stands only receive cash,  it would be great if they can have more POS machine, there is one suntrust ATM, but with transaction fee.

Quaint, unique, picturesque, and beautiful.  Pedestrian-friendly, pet-friendly, kid-friendly, walkable neighborhood, great farmer's market on Saturdays,  tree-lined streets, golf course views, great events, nature trails, beautiful parks, beautiful homes (unique and not cookie-cutter), great shops, and a quiet, relaxing atmosphere.  Wonderful place to live, work, and shop!
Looked cool, very clean and people seemed really nice!

When most developers clear cut all the trees down, the developers of Haile Plantation left most of them and built houses among the trees. You really appreciate the trees during the hot summer sun. Also, where else do you see paved walking and bike trails around a development. The trails are a wonderful asset. Then we have a quaint village. Not over developed. It’s just right.

Exceptional experience. Everything was impeccable and I couldn't have chosen a better destination for my birthday dinner. The kitchen accommodated our table's allergy.  Executive chef and owner Andy stopped by our table multiple times to make sure our party of 4 was enjoying our dinner, and he played a musical rendition of "Happy Birthday"  on the sax. My only regret is not trying Amelia's sooner.

Enjoyed an amazing time with family here Christmas night. The service was wonderful, the food had to have been the best I've ever had. I ordered the steak and shrimp with red potatoes covered in parmesan cream sauce and it was phenomenal. I am pregnant so had to order my steak cooked a little more than I typically would, and to my surprise, it was still so tender I could cut it with a spoon. My fiance actually proposed to me here and it was perfect. The owner/chef made rounds to check on each and every guest. The atmosphere is romantic and relaxing. I definitely recommend this restaurant for a nice evening out with your significant other. I can't wait to go again.

Drew was our server and he was great. We got two entrees from the Special and they were delicious (though a bit salty to us).
The chef came out to say hello at the end of our meal - it was pleasant.
 Will definitely come back again!

Amelia’s Restaurant is a must if you are in Gainesville and love Italian food. We make it a point to eat here whenever we are in town. The servers are wonderful and the food is amazing. The owner/chef is very friendly too. Highly recommend this restaurant.
Good service but food was very disappointing, especially for the reasonably high price charged. Interesting sounding dishes but very bland and unimpressive

Walkable distance from the UF campus! I used to have class in the business school area and would grab lunch there. The pizza is fresh and their rolls are THE BEST!! Very affordable prize and there are plenty of seatings available.

This place is my GO TO! during the week the do a lunch special where you get 3 rolls for 12$ or 2 for 9$ and it comes with soup and salad. It’s amazing! Their sushi is delicious and not pricey at all! I would definitely recommend this place to anyone.
Randomly walked over. Dragonfly had a 2 hour wait. Food was delicious and came out quickly/well prepared.  I now prefer Liquid Ginger over Dragonfly.

Always great atmosphere and great food. I recently went on NYE and the waiter forgot my friend's drink. No problem, I reminded a waiter in a different section and watched her tell the bartender. Still no drink. While the food came out at a good pace, the check took a while.
We love liquid ginger!! The service is fast, and food is awesome. Huge selection of drinks, sushi, and entrees. We’ve never disliked what we ordered off the menu. Highly recommend.

GREAT FOOD!! Go at lunch time. The prices are WAY less expensive than the dinner menu!! 2 sushi rolls for $9 or 3 for $12 and there's a variety to choose from. Also, their lunch meals come with soup and salad and you won't leave hungry!!!

It's good for what you need. An alternative to the regular downtown fair. But there falal is hard and to dry.

It's a shame because the used to be so good when the owner worked there.
Great Falafels. Always Fresh. Absolutely recommend this!
Falafel was so nice. I love the food and the great customer service there is amazing 👏😊
Good options for lunch and here we will get tasty grilled chicken with hummus.
Great lunch spot, super quick service and pretty delicious food.  Options for any falafel lover!

Great location. Friendly, understanding and knowledge staff. Although we knew what we wanted, others in our party had never been there and the staff was more than accommodating. A fire alarm sounded during our visit (due to another business in the plaza), and the staff was more than helpful in ensuring everyone was out and safe. They then came around and offered to refill drinks and kept us informed of situation and progress.

Once you understand how the menu works, everything is great. Service is friendly and very helpful, food ( I had a Medium size bowl of greens with lots of  toppings)  is fresh , tasty well  presented. A very popular lunch spot
Really good food, nice outdoor patio. Sushi rolls are great and not expensive. Of course benton boxes are good and lots of food.  Inside is a little too modern for me-black with blue lights.

Food was good. I really liked the poke bowl, and the green tea Bobba is always delicious. The music was a bit loud so if you are looking for a place to relax and talk this may not be the best place. However if you want to eat sushi and watch the game this is where you should go.
I've been to this location and the one on Archer a handful of times and I'm never disappointed. I love their poké bowls and tea, but you can't go wrong with anything on their menu!

Honestly, I’ve been passing by this place for many years, and I wrote it off like most of the garbage you expect to find advertised on highway billboards. Boy was I ever wrong. That first bite of their pulled pork made me cry. It took me right back to Little Havana in Miami. Everything on the menu is incredible, and everything on the menu is cheap. Entire meal was ten bucks. Thank you. I will be back.

They may be better in person.  I can only say that I will never use them again for a Group Order and Bite Squad Delivery.  The order process and Delivery by Bite was flawless.  I was ordering for 16 people.  The restaurant was "too busy" to put names on the orders, as requested, which led to ten minutes of chaos, crushed cartons and cold food.  It's a shame too, because I 'hear' the food is good.  My experience was very, very POOR.
exceptional Cuban food served authentic we in a wonderful environment. The service care so much for each individual that goes there. I would recommend at 100%
Love the coffee and the food. The fruit smoothies are amazing too. All reasonably priced and good customer service. Need to add a location in Tampa or Clearwater!
A quick stop on my way down to Florida. Friendly staff and great comfort food.

Food was great. Pricing not bad.
Service very good. My wife and I enjoyed all plus the setting. 
Highly recommend!

I love the atmosphere, the servers are awesome, and the prices are typical for this sort of place. The Shrimp Tiko was okay with the addition of salt & pepper. Blackened shrimp and a splash of heavy cream would've made it something special to write home about. 🙂 Lots more items on the menu to try so will def be going back.

Had the chicken Montego. The pasta + sauce was so bland, not even salt and pepper could save it. The chicken tasted like the bland, chicken patty "product" you get with hospital food. Nothing in this dish was fresh or tasty.
Amazing dining experience! The food was fresh and prepared extremely well! Can't wait to go again.

Now this place closed down for a few years and man was I bummed.  Different location.  The calamari costner was my favorite.  When I heard they came back I knew I had to see if the recipe changed.  Nope.  So good. They have other good items but I can't be a testimony to the other items.  This is the only pasta I'll get.  It's ridiculously delicious to me.  And I like it spiced up. Highly recommend.

THEIR LOCATION HAS MOVED!! DO NOT GO LOOKING FOR IT ON THE LOCATION LISTED ON GOOGLE. A more accurate location is: 203 SW 3rd Ave, right off Main St in the downtown area. Not positive, because I stumbled upon it when looking for parking in the area. The zucchini fries are the best, but the rest of the meal was just fair. A cool restaurant with trendy music and a cool vibe.

This place is awesome! Plenty of dishes to choose from and options to make them vegan or vegetarian if you need. The service is attentive and friendly and the wait time for food is impeccably fast, not to mention absolutely delicious. The pricing is very fair for quality and portion size. I am from out of town but would eat here all the time if I was a local.

Amazing food! Local art for sale on the walls. Incredibly good freshly made desserts. I cannot say a bad thing about this place! Breakfast all day! Locally sourced food! Vegan options! They are cash only though, so be prepared for that.

Food at the Jones has been hit or miss with me. The quality of some items on their menu is wildly inconsistent - for instance, the lox salmon breakfast sandwich is amazing, while the falafel burger arrived soggy and flavorless. I also wish the place were a little bigger--I feel cramped and clumsy in there. But I give them high marks for their effort. Despite these small flaws, My partner and I love to eat breakfast here, and they have amazing service. I hope the Jones stays around for a long time.
One of my favorite places in town. Generally all-local/organic type fare. Great breakfast and lunch. Haven't been yet for dinner. These people know how to make money. Cash only.

I've been here several times and have always had a great experience. The food tasted great and the staff was wonderful and helpful. It's a great looking restaurant with a lot of history on the walls. I got a chance to walk around and learn about all these cool different instruments that I've never heard of before. There's a lot of room, and it's a great atmosphere.
Beautiful restaurant, great parking. This is the place to book your private event.close to UF

All four stars are for ambience, they have beautifully captured the cinema, music and art of India in their interior decoration. Took forever for serving appetizer. Slow service although server was nice. Food was burnt. French fries with taste of sugar was a shocking surprise for you (may be Owner Is Gujarati originally). Would not recommend for authentic Indian food at all :(
Loved the food and the staff! Great people. The chicken tiki Masada is a great go to for first timers!

to start with, I have never been a fan of Indian food nor had much experience with any Indian restaurants, but my wife loves it, so we stopped in for lunch the other day. The restaurant is clean and festively decorated, my daughter loved the musical instruments on the walls. The food was awesome, I have had my culinary palate expanded and blown away - the food was flavorful and excellent. I had the tandoori hot chicken sandwich that was spicy and delicious. My daughter, who like all kids is an extremely picky eater had the chhole which she loved, and my wife's chicken tandoori was about the best chicken I have ever tasted. Service was excellent and all around a great experience, we will be back.
